<br>
Would like to see them add a focus effect to the orb for the 60+ pets, though. Maybe for the GVocs as well. That way folks who can't get into VT could have a focus item. I can't see how that would be too unbalancing, because the epic is still pretty tough to get. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=49757" target="blank"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://jupiterknight.virtualave.net/sig2.gif" style="border:0;"alt="Click to inspect me."/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=variathemage>Varia the mage</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 96<br> <font color=#333333>(12/5/02 7:51:25 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=851.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Solution for Epic pet</span><hr size=1> Like she said, the epic pet is very old and was amazing at the time it was introduced.  No item can be the best forever, so it is time to let the epic pet go once you get the new pets. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=108671">Varia Darselai</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> Arch Convoker</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=nenelar>Nenelar</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ballio.com/n.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 147<br> <font color=#333333>(12/5/02 7:58:41 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=851.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.ballio.com/nenclip.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Solution for Epic pet</span><hr size=1> I agree -- the epic pet was great for its time, but short of another epic quest series for ALL classes, I can't see mages getting special treatment.  For now, the epic pet is still a fine tank and damage dealer...and others have said it's only bested by the 65 pet for tanking. <p>Nenelar Valandur<br>
Arch Mage of E'ci<br>
Former Supporter of EZBoard</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=variathemage>Varia the mage</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 97<br> <font color=#333333>(12/5/02 8:29:53 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=851.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Solution for Epic pet</span><hr size=1> Oh I forgot to mention.  Just think about how over powering the mage epic would be if it was level 60 and boosted to the abilities of the 61+ pets.  Every other class in the game would scream and rightfully so. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=108671">Varia Darselai</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> Arch Convoker</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=northamevensong>Northam Evensong</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#333333>(12/5/02 8:39:24 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=851.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Solution for Epic pet</span><hr size=1> That and the dev's said at the last fanfaire that if epics were still useful beyond level 60 it was because they were overpowered to start with.<br>
<br>
Perhaps they will eventually get bored and make Epics v.2.0 if they aren't already in the game and just not found/announced yet.  And perhaps one part of the epic 2.0 will require epic 1.0 as a turn in. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
I must say that I am still looking forward to getting my epic for my mage. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   It has to be one of the best epics in the game, hands down. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ssslippy>SSSlippy</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_lightning.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Arch Mage</span><br>  Posts: 395<br> <font color=#333333>(12/8/02 2:11:03 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=851.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   I dont mind epic being gone</span><hr size=1> Its still the best pet pre 60.  Alot of melee epics have been replaced.  Casters have a bit more use for theres because they are effects and arnt as gear dependent as a melee is.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=nucci01>Nucci 01</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 30<br> <font color=#333333>(12/9/02 3:45:35 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=851.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: I dont mind epic being gone</span><hr size=1> The only problem I have with not upgrading the epic is the fact that the orb is pretty much useless if you don't use the pet. Many other class epics are still great items because they have mana free damage or buffs of some sort, what I'd like to see is the orb be changed to a buff instead of pet summoning. Make it a +1khps +50pt buff(no level change, no haste, no atk buff) That's not asking a lot really and would sort of help put the epic in balance for its level(lets face it, a 50 mage with epic is really powerful for their level). Im not going to cry over the epic getting outdated, but it would be nice for it to have some use in the upper levels.<br>
<br>
